        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(deepseek): recover V4 zero-cost spend",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #97047.\n\nDeepSeek V4 usage can still surface as zero spend through two related paths:\n\n- session transcripts may contain nonzero token usage with `usage.cost.total: 0`, which should be recomputed when the model has known positive pricing;\n- user-configured DeepSeek V4 model rows can carry an all-zero `cost` object, which previously counted as an explicit cost override and blocked hydration from the bundled DeepSeek catalog.\n\nThat combination can leave Control UI Spend and session log views reporting known-priced DeepSeek V4 usage as zero.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change keeps the generic session-cost guard from preserving recorded zero totals for known-priced nonzero-token usage, clears stale cost breakdowns so aggregation uses the recomputed estimate, and bumps the usage-cost cache version so older cached zero totals are rebuilt.\n\nIt also tightens the DeepSeek provider policy: catalog pricing now hydrates when the configured model has no positive cost values, while preserving explicit positive user cost overrides.\n\n## User Impact\n\nDeepSeek V4 spend summaries, cache rebuilds, and session logs now show estimated cost for known-priced token usage instead of a fabricated zero. DeepSeek V4 model configs with all-zero cost placeholders recover the bundled catalog pricing automatically.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` passed locally on the PR branch.\n- Added fixture coverage in `src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts` for known-priced DeepSeek V4 recorded zero cost, including summary totals, cache upgrade behavior, and `loadSessionLogs()` cost display.\n- Added fixture coverage in `extensions/deepseek/provider-policy-api.test.ts` for all-zero DeepSeek V4 cost hydration from catalog pricing.\n- Broader runtime validation should come from GitHub Actions on this PR head; no local broad test/build was run.\n\n## Related Work\n\nPR #97065 covers the core session-cost aggregation path for the same issue. This PR additionally covers DeepSeek provider catalog hydration for all-zero cost placeholders and keeps the session-log behavior aligned with the spend summary path.\n",
